eligibility_criteria.description:
Minimum age: 40 Years
Maximum age: 99 Years

The subject population to be studied in this protocol includes patients selected from CALGB-140202; all such patients have signed a written informed consent document meeting all federal, state and institutional guidelines as part of entry into that trial; the CALGB does not require that a separate consent form be signed for this study
International normalized ratio (INR) < 1.5 or activated partial thromboplastin time (aPTT) < 1.5 X upper limits of normal
Had evidence of central nervous system involvement of active AML
Patients must have a Mini Mental Status Exam score >= 15

Women of child-bearing potential must have a negative serum pregnancy at Screening
             and must agree to use an effective form of contraception from the time of the
             negative pregnancy test up to 3 months after the last dose of study drug. Effective
             forms of contraception include abstinence, hormonal contraceptive in conjunction with
             a barrier method, or a double barrier method. Women of non-child-bearing potential
             may be included if they are either surgically sterile or have been postmenopausal for
             ≥ 1 year.

groups.description: Patients receive one dose of erlotinib hydrochloride PO and then undergo standard "salvage" resection. Beginning 8-28 days after surgery, patients receive erlotinib hydrochloride PO QD on days 1, 8, 15, and 22. Courses repeat every 28 days in the absence of disease progression or unacceptable toxicity.

outcome_measures.measure: Frequency and severity of toxicity incidents assessed by Common Terminology Criteria version 2.0

outcome_measures.analysis_method: Will be assessed by comparisons using analysis of variance followed by paired t-test or other tests (Wilcoxon rank-sum test), if normality assumption is not satisfied even when data transformation is performed.
outcome_measures.measure: Change in Th1, Th2, and various immune regulatory cell populations in PBMC and assessed by flow cytometry
